column5: Pretty good entertainment, lot of fun to watch:clapping:

My gf watched the game for a minute then said to me: they aren't playing very well. Hahaha she thought it was a regular game.  Man, I'm probably missing the Junior game tonight I'll be watching a bonfire instead.
HaHa!,to see big John and the big E get that goal,brings back a few memories.The bonfire doesn't sound to bad Rod!

It should be ok...all that burned carbon for nothing. (hahah kidding) but I really want to see Canada whomp the U.S. Who do you think is going to play goal tonight?  ..and, Leafs Vs. Jets tonight. That should be a good game. They basically have the same record this year

It looks like Scott Wedgewood is getting the start. Who knows about the Toronto /Winnipeg game?. Toronto started well,Winnipeg not so much,and now there close in the points race. I personally hope Toronto can get back on track.
Would of been nice to see the great one show up for New York!,wonder what happened?
The Philly goalie, Little has the nicest pair of goalie pads I've seen in a long time!
Funny, I was thinking the same thing when Bernie was in.
